# Integrating AI APIs in .NET Core

In this guide, we'll explore how to integrate popular AI APIs like OpenAI and Grok into your .NET Core applications.

## Why AI Integration?

- Enhanced user experience with intelligent features
- Automation of repetitive tasks
- Real-time data processing and insights

## Step 1: Install NuGet Package

```bash
dotnet add package HttpClientFactory
```

## Step 2: Configure API Keys

```csharp
public class AiSettings
{
    public string GrokApiKey { get; set; }
    public string GrokApiUrl { get; set; }
}

// In appsettings.json
{
  "AiSettings": {
    "GrokApiKey": "your-key-here",
    "GrokApiUrl": "https://api.x.ai/v1"
  }
}
```

## Step 3: Create Service Wrapper

```csharp
public interface IAiService
{
    Task<string> GenerateText(string prompt);
}

public class GrokAiService : IAiService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _httpClient;
    private readonly string _apiKey;

    public GrokAiService(HttpClient httpClient, IOptions<AiSettings> settings)
    {
        _httpClient = httpClient;
        _apiKey = settings.Value.GrokApiKey;
    }

    public async Task<string> GenerateText(string prompt)
    {
        var request = new { prompt, max_tokens = 500 };
        var content = new StringContent(
            JsonConvert.SerializeObject(request),
            Encoding.UTF8,
            "application/json"
        );

        var response = await _httpClient.PostAsync("/chat/completions", content);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();

        var result = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
        return result;
    }
}
```

## Step 4: Register in DI Container

```csharp
services.Configure<AiSettings>(configuration.GetSection("AiSettings"));
services.AddHttpClient<IAiService, GrokAiService>();
```

## Step 5: Use in Your Application

```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("api/[controller]")]
public class AiController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly IAiService _aiService;

    public AiController(IAiService aiService)
    {
        _aiService = aiService;
    }

    [HttpPost("generate")]
    public async Task<IActionResult> GenerateText([FromBody] GenerateRequest request)
    {
        var result = await _aiService.GenerateText(request.Prompt);
        return Ok(new { response = result });
    }
}
```

## Error Handling

```csharp
try
{
    var result = await _aiService.GenerateText(prompt);
    return Ok(result);
}
catch (HttpRequestException ex)
{
    return StatusCode(500, new { error = "AI service unavailable" });
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    return StatusCode(500, new { error = ex.Message });
}
```

## Best Practices

- Always cache responses to reduce API calls
- Implement rate limiting
- Use dependency injection for testability
- Log all API interactions for debugging

## Next Steps

Try integrating with your existing .NET projects. Start with simple text generation, then move to more complex scenarios like chat applications.
